<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09026i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09026i">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09026i"> 26(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> transported to Thurles</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Provincial News in Brief.&hellip; Munster &hellip; &ldquo;Transported&rdquo; to Thurles</b>.&mdash;On Monday all the aged and infirm inmates of Borrisokane and Nenagh Unions were transferred in motor lorries and ambulance to Thurles Workhouse in view of amalgamation. One old lady observed in Nenagh Workhouse as she stepped in the lorry: &ldquo;May God forgive the men who are <mark>transporting us to Thurles</mark>, where we will never see the faces of our friends.&rdquo; <small> <a name="FJ21feb24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FJ21feb24"><cite title="source">Freeman's Journal</cite></a> (21 February 1924) 7/6</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Thurles is a market-town in Co. Tipperary, Ireland, but it is not a long way from Nenagh (24 miles). </mm> </dd></dl>
